Tenant of affordable housing development which was owned and operated by municipal public housing authority could assert claims against authority under \u167\'3f 1983 for violations of Violence Against Women Act (VAWA), arising from denial of housing assistance and eviction after tenant\rquote s husband, who was recipient of affordable housing vouchers for military veterans, removed tenant as voucher beneficiary; VAWA\rquote s housing protections were meant to benefit victims of domestic violence such as tenant, VAWA rights implicated in tenant\rquote s claim, i.e., prohibiting discrimination in housing based on domestic violence victim status and requiring notices of VAWA rights under enumerated circumstances, were not vague or amorphous and not otherwise incapable of enforcement by judiciary, and VAWA rights asserted by tenant were mandatory. 
