Tenant of affordable housing development which was owned and operated by municipal public housing authority sufficiently represented that she was entitled to protection under Violence Against Women Act (VAWA), as required to assert claims against authority under \u167\'3f 1983 for violation of VAWA, arising from denial of housing assistance and eviction after tenant\rquote s husband, who was recipient of affordable housing vouchers for military veterans, removed tenant as voucher beneficiary; although tenant did not provide authority with documentation that she was VAWA victim, she did represent to authority employee that she was, and authority did not present written request for such documentation. 
