Failure by municipal public housing authority, which owned and operated affordable housing development, to provide tenant with notice and hearing regarding her removal as beneficiary from her husband\rquote s housing vouchers for military veterans, violated tenant\rquote s procedural due process rights; tenant was beneficiary and therefore had property interest in affordable housing benefits, tenant lost all housing benefits, risk of erroneous deprivation of notice was high given fact that authority did not notify tenant, and requiring authority to provide tenant with some process would not be overly burdensome. 
