Under Washington law, failure by municipal public housing authority, which owned and operated affordable housing development, to comply with federal Violence Against Women Act (VAWA) and associated regulations, as required under rental agreement, constituted breach of contract, where authority terminated tenant\rquote s housing assistance following her removal as beneficiary from her husband\rquote s housing vouchers for military veterans and failed to provide necessary VAWA forms, and tenant was victim of domestic violence within meaning of VAWA, and thus was entitled to VAWA\rquote s protections under contract. 
