{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Under Washington law, municipal public housing authority, which owned and operated affordable housing development, was liable for conversion based on disposal of tenant\rquote s property left in rental unit following tenant\rquote s eviction; after authority executed writ of restoration and took possession of tenant\rquote s property, authority did not allow tenant opportunity to pay reasonable storage and drayage costs and retrieve her property, as required under state law, but instead provided tenant with balance that incorrectly included back rent which tenant was not required to pay, and authority did not give tenant any notice that her property would be destroyed. 
