Ms. Story\rquote s declaration is also contradicted by the deposition testimony of Defendant\rquote s own witnesses. Defendant\rquote s corporate designee Sarah Max testified on behalf of HASCO that she did not know whether pay or vacate notices included the necessary VAWA forms. (Crain Decl., Ex. 17 at 6.) Ms. Whittaker, who was personally involved in producing and delivering notices to Plaintiff, similarly testified that she did not know if anyone at HASCO gave Plaintiff a copy of the VAWA forms. (Crain Decl., Ex. 14 at 34.) Ms. Story\rquote s statement is further contradicted by Defendant\rquote s own answer, which admits that at least one of Defendant\rquote s notices did not provide any information related to VAWA. (Dkt. # 9 at \u182\'3f 22.) Without any effort to explain these discrepancies, Defendant \u8220\'3fcannot create an issue of fact by an affidavit contradicting [their] prior deposition testimony.\u8221\'3f 
