In addition, several related regulations on how to implement HUD housing programs govern an agency\rquote s duties when domestic violence occurs in a covered household. If a family breaks up because of domestic violence, the agency \u8220\'3fmust ensure that the victim retains assistance.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000547&cite=24CFRS982.315&originatingDoc=Ia5620cc005e911ef9201c1b632bece67&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul1 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
24 C.F.R. \u167\'3f 982.315
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Likewise, agencies must continue to assist tenants who are victims of domestic violence when recipients of VASH vouchers are the perpetrators of said violence, even if the victim would not be independently eligible to hold a VASH voucher:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li200 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li200 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li1000 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li1000 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa400 \sb600 
Generally, in the case of a family break-up, the HUD-VASH assistance must stay with the HUD-VASH veteran. However, in the case of domestic violence ... in which the HUD-VASH veteran is the perpetrator, the victim must continue to be assisted. Upon termination of the perpetrator\rquote s HUD-VASH voucher due to the perpetrator\rquote s acts of domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault, or stalking, the victim must be given a regular HCV if one is available .... If a regular HCV is not available for the victim, the perpetrator must be terminated from assistance, and the victim will continue to utilize the HUD-VASH voucher.
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
