Having considered all material undisputed facts in the light most favorable to Defendant, the Court finds that HASCO had a custom or practice of denying VASH vouchers to non-veteran victims of domestic violence, which violated Plaintiff\rquote s federal VAWA rights and resulted in her injury. Defendant\rquote s repeated assertion that Plaintiff could not hold a VASH voucher because she is not a veteran was incorrect. In fact, there are circumstances where a public housing agency must transfer the VASH voucher to a non-veteran victim of domestic violence or provide the victim with an alternative source of assistance. 
